<P>
   &UR; For FRIDAY PMs &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Here are the top news stories from The New York Times News
Service for PMs of Friday, July 16.
</P>
<P>
   The PMs news desk, 212-556-1927, opens at 7 a.m. Eastern Time.
To get story repeats before this hour call 212-621-1595 for reruns
on AP DataFeatures or 214-980-8305 or 8367 for repeats on UPI
DataNews.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IRAN-PROTESTS (Islamshar, Iran) _ In a working-class suburb of
Tehran where the government put down an economic protest a few
years ago, people clamor for jobs, not press freedom, and they're
just as disgruntled as the pro-democracy demonstrators. By Elaine
Sciolino.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-NOSTALGIA (Moscow) _ A Moscow journal on Russians'
increasing nostalgia for the Soviet era. A patina of nostalgia, or
at least kitsch, has spread over that gray world of communal
apartments, chronic shortages, propaganda slogans, controlled
newspapers and political taboos. By Serge Schmemann.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL _ GENERAL (Moved in ``a'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   COURT-SETTLEMENTS (Undated) _ More than a decade after states
began enacting laws to cut back big jury awards and curtail injury
lawsuits, state courts across the country are overturning one
measure after another, concluding that Americans have a powerful
right to settle their disputes in court. By William Glaberson.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BUSINESS DAY _ (Moved in ``f'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FASTER-COMPUTERS (Palo Alto, Calif.) _ Plunging deeply into a
microscopic world that promises ultrafast, low-power computers, a
team of Hewlett Packard Co. and UCLA researchers have for the first
time fashioned simple computing components no thicker than a single
molecule. By John Markoff.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo has been sent to NYT photo clients. Graphic has
been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   CORPORATE-SPONSORS (Portland, Ore.) _ The recent Portland Rose
Festival was kicked off by events like the Starlight Parade through
downtown. No, make that the ``Portland General Electric/Solv
Starlight Parade Presented by Southwest Airlines.'' Often, these
days, you can barely find the event for the sponsors. By Edwin
McDowell.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   INDEXFUNDS-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ For the past few years
investors have increasingly favored the mutual funds that track
stock market indexes, as few other funds have done better. But as
the performance of actively managed funds has come roaring back
this year, investors have begun throttling back their purchases of
index funds. By Richard A. Oppel Jr.
</P>
<P>
   ARDEN-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ Elizabeth Arden Co. received some
alarming news earlier this year when it heard the results of a
study of consumer attitudes about its company and the beauty
industry. For Arden, which has been struggling in a slow market
dominated by giant Estee Lauder Cos., it was a wake-up call. By
Patricia Winters Lauro.
</P>
