<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-16 00:41 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2246 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-COWBOYS-DRAFT-PIC     07-16 0326
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-DRAFT-PICKS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS GEAR UP TO NEGOTIATE WITH EIGHT DRAFT PICKS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ With training camp scheduled to begin in 10
days, Cowboys vice president Stephen Jones said the club will
likely extend initial contract offers to their eight draft picks
before the weekend.
</P>
<P>
   Despite the short window, Jones said he expects to have all the
players, including top pick Ebenezer Ekuban, signed and in camp on
time. Rookies and selected veterans are scheduled to report to
training camp in Wichita Falls on July 26.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's our goal,'' Jones said. ``We've just got to get it
done.''
</P>
<P>
   Jones won't have to worry about finding room under the league's
$57.28 million salary cap to sign any picks. Jones said the
Cowboys, who cleared $2 million by signing cornerback Deion Sanders
to a new deal last month, have enough money to sign the rookies and
still pursue some free agents before the start of the season Sept.
12.
</P>
<P>
   Jones, however, plans to focus on Ekuban, the former North
Carolina defensive end who is expected to get significant playing
time in a rotation with Greg Ellis and Kavika Pittman.
</P>
<P>
   Jones would not comment on what the Cowboys plan to offer
Ekuban. Ekuban's agent, Marvin Demoff, was unavailable for comment.
</P>
<P>
   A good benchmark for Ekuban, the 20th pick, is the contract
Green Bay defensive end Vonnie Holliday, the 19th pick in 1998,
signed last season. Holliday received a deal worth $5.61 million
over five years, including a $3 million signing bonus. Playing-time
incentives could increase the value of Ekuban's contract to $7.7
million.
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys vice president Jerry Jones Jr. will handle negotiations
with the other rookies _ guard Solomon Page, linebacker Dat Nguyen,
receiver Wane McGarity, defensive end Peppi Zellner, receiver
MarTay Jenkins, guard Kelvin Garmon and tight end Mike Lucky.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
