<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-16 01:49 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2278 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HKN-KINGS-LADN     07-16 0327
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-KINGS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KINGS SIGN DRAFT CHOICE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGER PHILLIPS  
 c.1999 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ With only a bit more than seven weeks remaining
until the start of training camp, the Los Angeles Kings chipped
away at their long list of unsigned players Thursday, getting
signatures from winger Steve McKenna and defenseman Frantisek
Kaberle.
</P>
<P>
   Both players signed one-year contracts. McKenna missed most of
last season with an abdominal injury, and Kaberle, 25, was selected
by the Kings in the third round of last month's NHL draft. The
6-foot-1, 185-pound Kaberle was named the most valuable defenseman
in Sweden last season, and the Kings are hoping for immediate
contributions from him.
</P>
<P>
   The Kings are hoping the 6-8, 247-pound McKenna, 25, will fill
the enforcer's role vacated by Matt Johnson, who was lost to
Atlanta in last month's expansion draft.
</P>
<P>
   The Kings' list of restricted free agents includes defenseman
Mattias Norstrom, winger Glen Murray and goalie Stephane Fiset.
Training camp begins Sept. 4 at Iceoplex.
</P>
<P>
   __ Red Wings sign Legace: Former Kings goalie Manny Legace
signed a multi-year contract with the Detroit Red Wings on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The move comes less than a week after Detroit's signing of free
agent goalie Ken Wregget as a backup to Chris Osgood.
</P>
<P>
   Legace, 26, played in 17 games with the Kings last season,
posting a 2-9-2 record with a 2.60 goals-against-average and a .911
save percentage. He was 22-18-4 with a 2.97 GAA in 47 games with
the Long Beach Ice Dogs last season, his fourth Minor League
season.
</P>
<P>
   ``He is an exceptional young goaltender and he will add more
depth to our goaltending position,'' Detroit general manager Ken
Holland said.
</P>
<P>
   The Red Wings lost three goalies in the past four months after
Bill Ranford was waived, Norm Maracle was lost in the expansion
draft and Kevin Hodson was traded to Tampa Bay.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
