<P>
   &UR; MOON WALK ANNIVERSARY: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Thirty years ago next week, much of the world listened to Neil
Armstrong's first words on the moon and pondered the implications
of his ``giant leap for mankind.'' It was a day for taking stock
and prophesying about the technological marvels and perils of the
future.
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday, July 14, we moved a series of photos to supplement
illustration of Apollo 11's historic mission. AP's PhotoExpress
clients will automatically receive NYT101-NYT104. Photos
NYT101-NYT109 are available to all photo clients at either the
Wieck Photo Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on
Newscom at 305-448-8411. Non-clients can make an individual
purchase by calling 888-603-1036 or 212-556-4204 or our Photo Sales
department at 212-556-1243.
</P>
