   NYHAN-COLUMN (Undated) -- The tendency of the Irish of Northern
Ireland to take our money -- but not our advice -- is again
ascendant in Ulster, where the peace agreement brokered so
painstakingly by two generations of American goodwill just
collapsed in a sea of Hibernian hypocrisy. By David Nyhan.
</P>
