<P>
   CARTOON-CHANNEL _ Turner Broadcasting will launch its second
cartoon channel on April Fool's Day next year. To be called
Boomerang, the channel also marks a redirection for the Cartoon
Network. It will focus on original cartoons while Boomerang will
feature old Hanna-Barbara cartoons. (Atlanta
Journal-Concstitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MINDSPRING-EARNINGS _ MindSpring shares up slightly after Dell
tells its shareholders meeting that an alliance with a U.S. ISP is
possible. However, analysts don't make much of the rumors and
MindSpring refuses to comment. (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   HUFFY _ Huffy Corp. says second-quarter earnings are way up, but
makes some cautionary statements about the state of its bicycle
business. (Hulsey, Dayton Daily News). 8.
</P>
<P>
   PRIMROSE _ ATLANTA _ Suburban Cartersville, Ga.-based Primrose
preschools (65 schools nationwide) has become one of the first
day-cares in the nation to gain accreditation from a group usually
associated with public schools and colleges. Primrose uses a
combination of teacher-directed and child-initiated learning from
infant to kindergartener. (Reinolds, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED
</P>
