He's a natural.'' Good politician? Natural campaigner? No. Good,
natural pancake flipper. And baby kisser, and hand shaker, and
autograph signer and patient listener _ even when a young man
insists on discussing the esoteria of soil conservation. By CRAGG
HINES.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-FILINGS (Austin, Texas) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush's aides
say his record $37 million presidential campaign finance report was
not filed electronically this week because the campaign was
discouraged from doing so by the Federal Election Commission. FEC
officials say, however, they actually encouraged the campaign to
file by computer. By R.G. RATCLIFFE. (Already filed.)
</P>
