<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; COSTPLUS _ &LR;  Five years ago, Oakland retailer Cost Plus was on the
verge of going under. But a smart management team helped whip it
into shape and it is now successfully rolling out stores across the
country. One of the retailer's greatest strengths is ironically the
thing that seems bizarre about it at first blush: its mix of
merchandise, which includes both home furnishings and gourmet food
and wine. Industry experts say the comestibles keep customers
coming back regularly, giving Cost Plus a competitive advantage
over its nearest competitor, Pier One, which carries similar home
goods but no food and wine. Cost Plus is giving Pier One a run for
its money as it expands outside California. By Carol Emert
</P>
