   &UR; EBAY  &LR;  _ Ebay is catering to the needs of its auction junkies
by offering its own browser built on Internet Explorer technology.
The EBay browser allows auction nuts to track bidding in progress.
The catch: It costs $19.95. By David Lazarus
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SCHWAB _ &LR;  Charles Schwab Corp. said its second-quarter profit
rose 98 percent, meeting expectations, and warned margins could
shrink as the largest Internet broker spends more on computers and
staff to satisfy demand. Net income rose to $151 million, or 18
cents a share, from $76.3 million, or 9 cents, in the second
quarter of 1998. Analysts in a First Call Corp. survey expected 17
cents a share. Revenue rose 53 percent to a record $982.1 million.
By Sam Zuckerman
</P>
