<P>
   ABOUT-CARS-PANOZ-ROADSTER (Undated) _ The first vehicle from
Panoz Auto Development, a somewhat austerely finished open-top
roadster that Danny Panoz describes as ``perfect for bikers''
rolled off the assembly line in 1992. With an outlandish hot
rod-retro body that makes the Plymouth Prowler seem conservative
and a monster V8 from Ford for muscle, the Panoz Roadster was bound
to turn a few heads. And of course, it graced the covers of
car-buff magazines with lots of pages to fill each year. But
curiosity quickly morphed into respect, with the early reviews
ranging from encouraging to ecstatic. Car and Driver has called it
``the best street-legal, turn-key, cottage-industry roadster
available in the United States.'' By Peter Passell. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Photo.
</P>
<P>
   CAR-SMART-ROADSTER (Undated) _ ``The AIV Roadster is a purist's
car, meant for one thing: driving,'' Danny Panoz warned, obviously
anxious that a test driver might write critically about his car's
lack of creature comforts. The $62,500 Roadster is, indeed,
ill-suited for a night at the opera _ or, for that matter, a trip
to the supermarket. By Peter Passell. (Moved).
